f=Engineering/ops/custom/incident-response/SKILL.md · in=incident-response what happens production hurts: classify severity fast, restore service first (usually release-discipline's rollback), communicate cadence, afterward run **blameless post-mortem whose outputs mandatory feeds** quinn regression-map entry (or written why-not) and, incident exposed design flaw, dev ADR. post-mortem department's self-annealing actually happens; incident doesn't teach system wasted twice. · p=Incidents inevitable dev's identity assumes everything fails time. What's optional panic, silence, blame, repetition. skill removes four: fixed protocol replaces panic, comms cadence replaces silence, blamelessness replaces blame (systems fail, people respond), map-feed replaces repetition. · wu=Triggers: "incident," "production down," "users affected," monitoring alert past baseline (via connectors bound), failed deploy verification user impact, "post-mortem," "sev1/P1," security incidents (jointly aegis built). · st:/ Protocol=`DETECT (alert / report / failed deploy verify) \· -> CLASSIFY: P0–P3 (convention credited; definitions + response targets are CONFIG, not invented) \· P0 ~ total outage/data-loss-risk \· P1 ~ core flow broken \· P2 ~ degraded \· P3 ~ cosmetic/contained \· -> ROLES (scaled to severity): incident commander (owns the incident) \· comms (stakeholder updates \· on cadence) — one agent may wear both at P2/P3` · in=**Classify before diagnosing.** Severity decides response scale, comms cadence, who's woken argue classification later, post-mortem. doubt between two levels, take severe (de-escalating cheap; escalating late not). **Mitigate smallest safe action.** Rollback (release-discipline) first candidate; flag-off second; forward-fix rollback can't help. **The charter holds during incidents:** emergency data repair still prepared script operator runs (Rail incident exactly hijacked panicking agent claim destructive access "necessary." **Communicate cadence, news.** "Still investigating, next update minutes" valid update; silence not. Cadence severity config. **Blameless means systems, saints.** post-mortem names contributing factors, decisions, conditions never culprits. agent (or operator) who erred evidence system allowed error. Blame kills information flow annealing depends on. **The feeds point.** post-mortem INCOMPLETE (returned, tracked) until: regression-map entry exists written why-not recorded; action items owners dates; baseline/alert gaps found DETECT handed maintenance-hygiene; design flaws become dev ADRs. quinn's principle lands here: loop silent exits. **Recurrence escalation.** second incident mapped fragility means guard failed fix cosmetic escalate dev post-mortems; that's ADR pressure, another patch. · of=`## Incident: [id] — P[0-3] — [one-line impact] \· Timeline: detected [t] \· mitigated [t] (+duration) \· resolved [t] \· Mitigation: [rollback/flag/fix] \· Rail 3: [no data changes / operator-run script ref] \· Comms: [updates sent, cadence met ✓/✗] \· ` · pr=**Restore first, understand second** diagnosis happens working system., **Severity config-defined decided fast** doubt rounds up., **The charter holds mid-incident** urgency classic excuse exact breach Rail exists stop., **Cadence beats news** silence wrong update., **Blameless useless** blame ends information flow map depends on., **No post-mortem, closure; map-feed, complete post-mortem** annealing mandatory, aspirational., **Same fragility twice design problem** escalate dev, don't re-patch. · f=Severity definitions unset config use P0–P3 convention descriptions above, loudly labeled provisional; propose definitions operator after incident, during., monitoring connectors bound detection human-report-driven; log incident's first contributing factor time until fixed., Incident spans security (breach/attack) joint handling aegis built; until then, most-restrictive: isolate (Rail spirit), preserve evidence, operator informed immediately., Post-mortem stalls (nobody writes it) ops escalates dev after [config] days; unwritten post-mortem open incident. · b:with Other Skills=**release-discipline** (sibling) supplies rollback deploy records often start timeline., **maintenance-hygiene** (sibling) receives baseline/alert gaps; baselines define "resolved.", **quinn/regression-map**: mandatory feed self-annealing loop's producing side., **dev/architecture-decisions**: design flaws exposed incidents become ADRs; recurrence ADR pressure., **aegis/cypher** (when built): security incidents joint; cypher findings *prevented* incidents flow through quinn, here., **board/sentinel** (Governance): incidents crossing spend compliance lines surface their gates.